00:36:55.626 --> 00:36:57.376
none of the wrinkles
are arbitrary.

00:36:57.376 --> 00:37:01.216
All of them flow exactly
where the skin would fold

00:37:01.216 --> 00:37:02.366
and compress over time.

00:37:02.966 --> 00:37:05.516
And so, I can't just
paint these willy-nilly.

00:37:05.516 --> 00:37:06.656
I have to really make sure

00:37:06.656 --> 00:37:09.906
that they are feeling what we
would call motivated, right?

00:37:09.946 --> 00:37:12.666
That they would be--
they would be naturally

00:37:12.666 --> 00:37:14.216
where the character
would be wrinkling.

00:37:14.216 --> 00:37:15.846
Now, this is obviously
a made up character.

00:37:15.846 --> 00:37:18.236
But the character still has
to feel believable, right?

00:37:18.296 --> 00:37:20.726
If this character
creature were to exist,

00:37:21.366 --> 00:37:22.726
how would she wrinkle
in her face?

00:37:22.956 --> 00:37:25.086
So, I'm good with these.

